# ChainBa design system

## Stack
React 18 CRA, plain CSS, ethers.js v6, no React Router (page state machine in App.js)

## Colors
- Primary CTA: #10B981 emerald
- Accent: #6366F1 indigo  
- Hero background: #0A0E1A navy
- Content light: #F8FAFC ice white
- Text: #0F172A headings, #334155 body, #64748B muted

## Typography
- Headlines: Playfair Display, weight 700, letter-spacing -1.5px
- Body: DM Sans, weight 300 paragraphs / 500 labels
- Numbers/code: DM Mono
- One italic + emerald word per headline

## Spacing & radius
- Cards: border-radius 20px
- Buttons: border-radius 10px
- Hero mockup: border-radius 24px
- Section padding: 7rem 3rem

## Animation rules
- Scroll reveal: IntersectionObserver, opacity 0→1 + translateY(30px→0)
- Easing: cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1), duration 700ms
- Stagger siblings: 120ms delay each
- Card hover: translateY(-4px) + colored box-shadow
- Never use parallax or physics engines

## React rules — CRITICAL
- NEVER call hooks inside .map() or any callback
- Every card that uses useReveal() must be its own named component
- FeatCard, StepCard, MemberCard, PathCard — all separate components
- CSS in companion .css file, never @import in CSS
- Fonts via <link> in public/index.html only

## Page state machine
App.js uses setPage() not React Router.
Navigate between pages: onNavigate prop passed down.
Protected pages check: account || backendUser?.walletAddress

## Git commit conventions
Always use conventional commits format:

feat:     new feature or page
fix:      bug fix
style:    visual/CSS changes only, no logic
refactor: code restructure, no behaviour change
chore:    config, dependencies, tooling
docs:     README, comments only

Examples:
  feat: add GroupView redesign with cycle progress
  fix: replace hardcoded IP with BASE_URL in Login.js
  style: update Dashboard card hover states
  refactor: extract MemberCard as separate component
  chore: add chainba design tokens to cursor rules

Rules:
- Subject line max 72 characters
- Use present tense: "add" not "added"
- No period at end
- Reference the page/component affected
- Never commit "fix stuff" or "update" alone
